<br>
First off, experience groups.<br>
If I am tanking an exp mob that hits for under 900 and goes enrage and is slowed, I sit down and taunt.  Nothing like sit aggro.<br>
<br>
Hits for more than 300 and is not slowable...duck, taunt, beg, disarm...Whatever I can do to get it's attention.<br>
<br>
Hits for more than 900.  Whether slowable or not.  I simply take out the 2hs and start slashing away while taunting.  I keep AoE taunt up only for 2 reasons.  I lose aggro on a mob that hits for more than 1200 or multiple mobs turning my casters into ground beef.  Not for losing aggro on an exp mob.<br>
<br>
There are diff situations, but those are some main ones. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=warblayde>warblayde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/2/03 1:46:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you do when tanking an enraged mob?</span><hr size=1> Im sorry but im pretty new to the high lvl mobs here. What is enranging, or what does a mob do when he enrages? And why would you beg and or duck when a mob enrages?<br>
