<br>
Do ENRAGED mobs not do normal melee attacks? For 10 seconds the mob just stops attacking and hopes someone in it's frontal arc hits it so it can riposte back on their fool self??<br>
<br>
If so, then the stuff about sitting, taunting/begging/disarming, taunting mezzed mobs, etc. all makes sense.<br>
<br>
And lastly, what all can a mob &quot;do&quot;? I always forget..<br>
<br>
There is:<br>
ENRAGE: 10 sec auto-riposte<br>
RAMPAGE: hit all ppl in frontal arc once (?)<br>
FLURRY: kinda like a multiple-attack hit except it can happen within a multiple attack. Like, mob_swing_01, mob_flurries, mob_flurry_01, mob_flurry_02, mob_flurry_03, mob_swing_02, mob_swing_03, (?)<br>
